    <note>Hu(1) Cheng [13133] Hu Quan, WJ, 30.5a-6a. Here Hu(1) Quan [10565] notes he was Cheng's lineage younger cousin (zudi), which is one explicit reference to the connection between the a and b branches of this lineage. In the funerary inscription for Cheng's son, Yun, he is more explicit and identifies Cheng as the grandson of Quan's second granduncle, which would make Cheng a third cousin, and Cheng's great great grandfather the father of both Cheng's great grandfather and Quan's great grandfather.</note>
